    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="308"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Eustis</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Presume change in your note relates to phraseology, not substance. Can you not
                    ascertain whether pardon on terms specified will be acceptable to Waller? Shall
                    confer with his counsel on that subject. Trust to hear from you definitely, and
                    at once, that proposition of French Government has been made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
